    <preface>
      <longTitle>
        <p><docTitle>Committee on Gastronomy Session: Hearing on Paella Reform</docTitle></p>
      </longTitle>
      <p>Session of June 5, 2024 of the Parliamentary Committee on Gastronomy.</p>
      <p>Subject: Review of the <ref href="/akn/poc/bill/paella-reform-2024">Paella Reform Bill</ref>. Expert witness hearing.</p>
    </preface>

    <debateBody>
      <debateSection eId="dbsect_apertura" name="opening">
        <heading>Opening</heading>
        <speech eId="speech_1" by="#presidenta">
          <from>Committee Chair</from>
          <p>The session of the Committee on Gastronomy is called to order. Today we welcome Chef Ramon Expert to discuss the technical aspects of the <ref href="/akn/poc/bill/paella-reform-2024">reform bill</ref>.</p>
        </speech>
      </debateSection>

      <debateSection eId="dbsect_audiencia" name="hearing">
        <heading>Expert witness hearing</heading>
        <speech eId="speech_2" by="#chef">
          <from>Chef Ramon Expert</from>
          <p>Thank you, Madam Chair. As a chef with 30 years of experience, I can confirm that bomba rice has unique absorption properties. However, a good round-grain rice can yield acceptable results.</p>
          <p>Regarding seafood, it is technically incompatible with the cooking times of chicken and rabbit. Mixing them compromises both textures.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech eId="speech_3" by="#madrilena">
          <from>Rep. Madrid</from>
          <p>Chef, but is it not true that millions of families already prepare paella with seafood?</p>
        </speech>
        <speech eId="speech_4" by="#chef">
          <from>Chef Ramon Expert</from>
          <p>They prepare rice with seafood, which is excellent. But technically it is not Valencian paella. The representative's bill at least proposes the designation 'mixed paella', which I find reasonable.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech eId="speech_5" by="#valenciano">
          <from>Rep. Valencia</from>
          <p>Exactly! The chef confirms our position. The <ref href="/akn/poc/doc/gastronomy-committee-report">committee report</ref> must reflect this technical distinction.</p>
        </speech>
      </debateSection>

      <debateSection eId="dbsect_cierre" name="closing">
        <heading>Closing</heading>
        <speech eId="speech_6" by="#presidenta">
          <from>Committee Chair</from>
          <p>We thank the Chef for his testimony. The committee will issue its <ref href="/akn/poc/doc/gastronomy-committee-report">report</ref> before the <ref href="/akn/poc/debate/plenary-paella-reform">plenary debate</ref>. The session is adjourned.</p>
        </speech>
